commit.message:
Refactor: remove smoketests

As notus-scanner is getting superseeded by openvasd
https://greenbone.github.io/scanner-api/#/notus/notus_run
which is already intergrated in openvas:
https://github.com/greenbone/openvas-scanner/commit/7bf3fa7f6d8d3880568878fffeafa5c66e5c931d

and will be updated in the community images within the next major
version of openvas.

As preparation this commit removes the failing smoketests as they are
creating security alerts with codeql.

commit.message:
Fix: Use better defaults for example config

Kali used this example for their config and the log file should be in
/var/log/gvm beside all other logs from our software stack. Additionally
/var/run is just a symlink to /run.

Change: Don't fork notus-scanner in service file

There is no need to use forking with systemd. We already changed all
other services to run in "foreground".
Ignore ruff's cache from git

Change: Replace isort and pylint with ruff

ruff is just sooooooo much faster.
Change: Update copyright header for 2024

Change: Fix installation section in README

Using poetry is only necessary for doing development. Point users to the
INSTALL.md directly.

Change: Improve formatting in INSTALL.md

Remove trailing newlines and auto format markdown.
Change: Update copyright in README

Change: Update README for linking to the forum

Our forum is on forum.greenbone.net nowadays.

Change: Update README regarding required Python version

Python >= 3.9 is required since a while.

Remove: Remove changelog generation files

Use the default changelog config and drop the generated changelog fo the
22.4.0 release. It's always possible to generate this file manually via
`pontos-changelog`.
Change: Update black excludes for non existing dirs

Change: Merge coveragerc file into pyproject.toml

Put the coverage config into pyproject.toml.

Add: Add coverage as dev dependency

It is required to calculate the coverage and was missing.

Change: Use group dev instead of dev-dependency for poetry

The dev-dependencies got deprecated and replaced by generic groups with
poetry >= 1.2.0.

Remove: Let users decide where to store the created venv

Remove the poetry.toml config file to let the users decide where poetry
will create the virtual environment. It may desirable to not create the
venv within the project directory.
Auto format pyproject.toml

Add: Support Python 3.12

Add support for Python 3.12.
Change: Use trusted publisher upload for PyPI
